1
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:45,200
<i>In eight more hours, we will witness</i>

2
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:48,080
<i>the grand reunification ceremony</i>
<i>of Hong Kong and China.</i>

3
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:52,240
<i>This is a moment we have</i>
<i>been waiting for 155 years.</i>

4
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:52,920
WELCOME BACK, HONG KONG

5
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:58,720
<i>The midnight of July 1st, 1997</i>
<i>is approaching steadily.</i>

6
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,800
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

7
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:15,320
What was it again? Good

8
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:18,240
afternoon, Sir.

9
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:31,080
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

10
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:48,640
No parking here.

11
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:51,160
No parking here. Go.

12
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,880
‪Hey!

13
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,680
Where did she go?

14
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,760
A relative of someone here?

15
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:10,280
Look. That guy.

16
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:10,960
NEW YORK BLOCK

17
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,120
Why is he in black?

18
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,480
They didn't even pick up the kid
after they bumped into him.

19
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,520
Qiang.

20
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,520
Qiang.

21
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,320
Eighteenth floor?

22
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,360
I thought no one lived there anymore.

23
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:06,000
Qiang.

24
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:13,640
Do you see what's on her back…

25
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:14,960
- What are you staring at?
- Oh my!

26
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:16,720
Nothing.

27
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,240
I have a meeting at the provincial office.

28
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:21,000
Keep your eyes open.
Make sure nothing happens.

29
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,120
Okay.

30
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,960
The janitor said she went
to the 18th floor.

31
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,320
18th floor? It's already haunted

32
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,600
before they raided
the prostitution rings here.

33
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,920
Eighteenth floor?
Wasn't the underground club raided?

34
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,200
Where did they go?

35
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,120
It's you, Ma Qiang?

36
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:34,880
Weird. Both fire exits are locked.

37
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,800
Where could those two have gone?

38
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,360
Don't touch anything.
Go downstairs to find them.

39
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,880
What's the matter, Wang?

40
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,360
Wang Wuluan. What are you doing?

41
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:02,760
Why is there a pair of footprints here?

42
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,040
There's no one in there.

43
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:49,360
Call 110!

44
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:03,240
Puking before you go to work.

45
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:07,400
This must be your first day, rookie.

46
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,960
I'm getting motion sickness.
You drove too fast.

47
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:14,240
Liu. After you're done puking,
come here. I want to talk to you.

48
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:16,880
Come here. I want to talk to you.

49
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,760
Listen.

50
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,440
Listen.

51
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,960
We've been asked
to team up at the last minute.

52
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:32,080
Even though it's quite ad hoc,
rules must be established.

53
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,440
I know. Captain Feng said
you came to assist

54
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,800
and would go back after a week.

55
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,040
- They asked me to…
- They asked you

56
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,600
not to give me any trouble. Right?

57
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:41,920
They asked me to guide you
through our work.

58
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,960
Who's guiding whom now? You're a rookie.

59
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,920
Do you know how many years
I've been doing this?

60
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:51,720
But you've been working
in a police station.

61
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,480
I studied for six years to become
a criminal police officer.

62
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,440
You only know the theories.

63
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:57,960
Enough chatting.

64
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,600
The old guide the young.
That's the rule in the squad.

65
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,680
Captain Feng only told me
to partner up with you.

66
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:05,200
Even in a partnership,
there's a pecking order.

67
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,880
I'm the mentor. You're my apprentice.

68
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:09,120
When we work, you listen to me.

69
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,520
So, how do you want to proceed today?

70
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,800
That's the right attitude.

71
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:21,640
Listen. I was in charge of Yuanlongli
when I was working in the police station.

72
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:24,040
Back then, the workers dug out a cenotaph.

73
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:27,880
After that, the residents
became paranoid and superstitious.

74
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,560
They keep calling the police for nothing.

75
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:33,000
- So?
- So, we stay put.

76
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,559
We let them cool their heads.

77
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,000
I disagree.

78
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:39,799
If paranoia isn't solved in time,
it might evolve into a collective risk.

79
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:42,320
Did I just establish
the pecking order for nothing?

80
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,480
I'm your mentor. You're my apprentice.

81
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:46,320
- If I tell you to do this…
- Mr. He.

82
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,160
Can we work now?

83
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:51,760
Mr… Mr. He? You think I'm a mechanic?

84
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,480
More like someone who fixes gas lights.

85
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,600
What gas lights?

86
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:56,440
Gaslighting. Gaslight.

87
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,000
Did you just tell me to bugger off?

88
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,520
So rude.

89
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:08,920
Something bad happened
in Yuanlongli just now.

90
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,440
Do you want to know?
A woman was carrying a man on her back

91
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,560
up to the 18th floor.

92
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,080
How creepy!

93
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:17,760
A man and a woman.

94
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:20,240
Both covered in black.

95
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,160
Gone.

96
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,200
Not even bones left.

97
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:25,280
I saw with my own eyes.

98
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,880
You saw with your own eyes.

99
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,680
Meng. Come here.

100
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:37,760
Not even bones left. I see.

101
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:40,680
Officer He. That's my cloak.

102
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:42,520
Didn't you say it killed two people?

103
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,640
It's now evidence.

104
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,320
I have to keep it to examine it.

105
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,160
Who else witnessed it?

106
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,880
‪YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

107
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,280
‪POLICE

108
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,320
Calling the police
for the slightest inconvenience.

109
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,600
How many times has it been?

110
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:01,200
You two.

111
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,800
One is from the residents committee.
One is from the security team.

112
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:05,880
Instead of dispelling
the superstition, you fanned it.

113
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:08,160
Making a fake police call is a crime.
Do you understand?

114
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,640
Yes.

115
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:11,840
There's no victim and no culprit.

116
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,360
Their relatives
also didn't call the police.

117
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,120
There's nothing to file a case here.

118
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,000
Besides, the police already came here.

119
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:19,360
Come. Sign it.

120
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:23,840
One more week,
and I'll go back to my previous post.

121
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:26,200
Do you get what I mean?

122
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,920
It's the last sprint.

123
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,680
Don't go to the criminal department
and bother me for something trivial.

124
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:31,920
If I get a case,
I won't be able to go back.

125
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,600
- Just sign it.
- I… Where do I sign it?

126
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,200
This young man is…

127
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:41,280
Oh, he's Liu. My apprentice.

128
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:42,920
He just graduated.
It's his first day at work.

129
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,200
He's new here.
Do look after him, will you?

130
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,920
Hello. I'm Ran. R-A-N.

131
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,040
Also, I'm not his…

132
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,560
WITNESS' STATEMENT

133
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:05,200
Hi. Are you Li Tieling?

134
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:08,200
So the woman and the old man
disappeared when you turned around.

135
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,640
Yes. The woman was wearing a white dress
and blue leather heels.

136
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,320
She vanished just like that.

137
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:15,680
- Do you want to know how they vanished?
- Yes.

138
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,000
Re-enact what you did
when you chased the rickshaws away.

139
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,040
Then turn around and look at me.

140
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:23,280
Okay. No parking here. Go. Go.

141
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,200
Are you insane?

142
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,120
Then I…

143
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,560
He's gone. He's gone.

144
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,960
I'm here.

145
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,680
You assumed they would cross
the main road to enter the gate.

146
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:37,000
But they stuck to the wall,

147
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:38,760
just outside your line of vision.

148
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,560
This is called a psychological blind spot.

149
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,080
Watch me do it again.

150
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,520
You explained the trick.

151
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,520
Why bother doing it again?

152
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,480
It's called re-enactment.

153
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:53,000
According to the Western
investigation procedures,

154
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:56,120
you must imagine that you're the culprit
and re-enact what they did.

155
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:57,440
Enact what?

156
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,800
Re… enact?

157
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:04,200
From this place to that block,
taking the main road is the shorter route.

158
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,920
Why did they take a detour then?

159
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,240
Come with me.

160
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:13,880
Where are we going?

161
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,280
Case closed.

162
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,920
They didn't ask for criminal police.

163
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,520
Captain Feng got a call and asked us
to assess the situation personally.

164
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,480
We didn't even enter the premises.
Isn't that too irresponsible?

165
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:24,240
Irresponsible?

166
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:26,240
Making a fake police call
is irresponsible.

167
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,640
It's a waste of police resources too.

168
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:32,480
Sir, we over-reacted here. Please go back.

169
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,800
I'll just talk to Officer Qu.

170
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,680
Wait. Officer Qu?

171
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:37,560
Which one? Qu Dahai?

172
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:41,960
Yes. I called 110, and Officer Qu came.

173
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:42,880
He's inside the building?

174
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:45,560
I'll go and take a look.

175
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:55,320
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

176
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,800
That woman carried the old man

177
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:02,600
and stood still here.
She even took off her heels.

178
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,240
What else did she do?

179
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,760
She did this.

180
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,040
I can fix it.

181
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:22,960
I'll pick it up.

182
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:35,000
So clumsy. Hurry up.

183
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:42,880
Officer Qu. Careful. The footprints.

184
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,360
What are you doing?

185
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,120
PATTIA CLUB

186
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:56,080
He Yuanhang. What brings you here?

187
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:59,080
Han. Shouhu.

188
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,560
What are you doing here? Go back.

189
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:02,520
Did I say you could go back?

190
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,560
Continue.

191
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:05,400
Your footsteps are making a mess.

192
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:08,640
Are you examining
or contaminating the crime scene?

193
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,120
Who says I'm examining the scene?

194
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,320
I'm looking for the culprit. Continue!

195
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:15,040
Touch anything if you dare.

196
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,520
Excuse me. You're blocking the evidence.

197
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,360
See? The criminal police are working.

198
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,640
Now work!

199
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:25,760
You little…

200
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:40,840
I like him. What's his name?

201
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,600
Ran Fangxu. My apprentice.

202
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,200
Top scorer from People's Public Security
University of China, PPSUC.

203
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:48,400
PPSUC?

204
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,000
Your apprentice?

205
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,960
Why would I have
brought him here with me, otherwise?

206
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:54,840
Jealous?

207
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,680
Want to join the criminal department?

208
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:59,400
I can talk to Captain Feng for you.

209
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:02,400
You can have him.

210
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,200
Sounds good?

211
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,440
This wooden plank is so annoying.

212
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,680
Well, it's all thanks to your mentor.

213
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:20,560
He did this when he raided
the prostitution ring.

214
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,840
That's right.

215
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:26,920
Let me borrow this.

216
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,640
He is not my mentor.

217
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,120
You liar.

218
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,680
- Ma Qiang.
- Yes.

219
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:41,600
- Open the door.
- Okay.

220
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,600
Forgive me. I conducted an experiment.

221
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:51,680
What are you doing?

222
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:55,200
Seriously? It's called enaction. Right?

223
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,560
Re-enactment.

224
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:03,240
There's a nail on the door frame.

225
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,920
The dust by the door frame is gone.

226
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,040
I suppose someone
hung the black cloak here.

227
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:12,880
The height of it is enough
to cover an adult

228
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,640
when someone opens the door.

229
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:16,800
A prank then?

230
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:18,640
But there's one unanswered question.

231
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,400
The footprints disappear here.

232
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,280
They didn't go back the way they came.

233
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,120
Qu Dahai and his men stepped
all over the place.

234
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,320
How can we trace footprints now?

235
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,600
Dust can be thick.

236
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:30,000
New and old footprints have gaps.

237
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,920
You're so thorough, Fangxu.

238
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,040
You left no stone unturned.

239
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:36,200
Unlike someone I know
who has peanuts for a brain.

240
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,360
All empty inside.

241
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,320
You have peanuts for a brain.

242
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,240
Move.

243
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,680
How can you be a criminal police
with such a bad core strength?

244
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,160
Size 37 feet.

245
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:51,920
Carrying an old man
all the way from outside.

246
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,080
She must be a strong woman.

247
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:00,240
These must be the basics
you learned in PPSUC.

248
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,760
They don't teach you common sense.

249
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:05,920
You little…

250
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,880
What did you see?

251
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,520
Four cigarette butts.

252
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:25,240
Judging from their looks,

253
00:17:25,319 --> 00:17:27,359
they were used less than two hours ago.

254
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:31,560
Judging from the charred ends,
the smoker was anxious.

255
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,600
Some of them were thrown away
after a few puffs were taken.

256
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,920
Do you recognize the brand?

257
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,280
How much does it cost?

258
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,520
A packet of Yuxi cigarettes.

259
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:46,200
Mainly for bosses.
Twenty yuan for one packet.

260
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:57,280
Are you sure there were
no footprints in the room?

261
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,840
I guess so.

262
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,600
We came looking for the culprit.

263
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,240
Of course, we walked around.

264
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:09,760
Then don't walk that much.

265
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:22,440
‪BEIJING TRAVEL

266
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:28,520
Officer He. Officer Qu.

267
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,400
Calm down. Tell me clearly.

268
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:34,520
Okay. I checked all the rooms.
There's no one.

269
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:37,320
I also checked the security cameras.
No one took the elevator.

270
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:41,520
Two adults couldn't possibly
vanish just like that.

271
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:42,960
They must be somewhere.

272
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:44,880
Both sides of the staircase
are locked from the outside too.

273
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,800
Where else could they go?

274
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,880
It looks like a locked room.

275
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:51,400
Three paths.

276
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,640
The staircase is locked.

277
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:55,920
The elevator has security cameras.

278
00:18:56,000 --> 00:19:00,000
Exactly. It's weird.
That's why I called Captain Feng.

279
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:04,720
I think you should file a case.

280
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:07,800
File what case? What case?

281
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:09,640
Let me explain everything to you.

282
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:13,080
The door is locked from the outside.
You can't open it.

283
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:29,120
See? They left like this.

284
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,760
This door isn't locked.

285
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:32,400
File a case?

286
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,360
This is just a prank. Okay?

287
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,440
Officer He. This isn't right.

288
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:38,320
The staircase. The window.

289
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,440
And the padlock. The padlock!

290
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:42,400
What? Isn't it…

291
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:47,400
- Surround them from both sides!
- On it!

292
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,840
Stay right there!

293
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:04,840
Wait for me.

294
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:07,360
Sorry, I'm in a hurry.
Take the next one. Sorry.

295
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,760
Stealing a lock before the police.

296
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,280
How dare you!

297
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:11,480
Stop right there.

298
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,400
Stop right there. Stop right there.

299
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,160
What are you doing?

300
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:45,840
He Yuanhang!

301
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:48,120
I caught him. He Yuanhang! Help me!

302
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:49,360
Why are you yelling?

303
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,000
Stop yelling.

304
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,400
You took the elevator,
but you're still slow!

305
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:53,680
He has already run away!

306
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,040
Be careful.

307
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,040
NEW YORK BLOCK

308
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,680
Officer He!

309
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,880
Officer He. Officer He.

310
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,560
There are bad guys in the block.

311
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:12,240
They scared my son.

312
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:15,960
Were you running around
the staircase just now?

313
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:19,640
Why did you go to the 18th floor?

314
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,480
He saw everything.

315
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,640
He even bumped into them.

316
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:24,800
Tell me.

317
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,600
Why did you lock us in the staircase?

318
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:29,800
I was scared you'd come after me.

319
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,640
Hey there. It's okay.

320
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:37,000
You saw the two missing persons, right?

321
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,000
I saw their hands.

322
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:43,040
It's not human hands. They have claws.

323
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:53,800
Claws?

324
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:56,120
Is that coming from your exaggeration?

325
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:04,360
See? I told you so.

326
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,440
They bumped into him,

327
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:08,000
and they didn't even pick him up.

328
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:10,400
They bumped into him how many times?

329
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:11,320
Just once.

330
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,000
And he got bruises everywhere?

331
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:14,800
It's as if he has been run over.

332
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:18,080
- Little one, your bruises are…
- I fell when he chased after me.

333
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:28,920
Officer He. Listen.

334
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,920
We put the padlock
when we were checking the place.

335
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,840
I don't care who put it there.
I just want to know if it was locked.

336
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,040
No, it wasn't.

337
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:36,960
It wasn't locked?

338
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:39,520
That means those two people
could leave through that door.

339
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:41,400
I guess so.

340
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:48,520
You examined the place for hours,

341
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:51,200
and you couldn't figure out
one simple staircase.

342
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:53,520
Qu. Given your lack of competence,

343
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,320
how am I supposed
to put in a few good words for you?

344
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:57,080
Say no more.

345
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:02,440
Don't just stand there.
This is just a prank.

346
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:03,880
Go back and pack up. Case closed!

347
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:07,120
I already told you so.

348
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:09,160
The reunification of Hong Kong
is more interesting.

349
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:15,520
Officer He. We need to file a case.

350
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:27,560
Then explain. Why?

351
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:30,320
Ma Qiang said there were
no footprints in the western corridor.

352
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,760
They also said the cloak
took two people away.

353
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:34,320
They make things up all the time.

354
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,480
How can I believe them?

355
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,280
Be patient. Let me finish.

356
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:39,600
Just tell me what you want to do.

357
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,360
I just want to get to the bottom
of this case.

358
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:44,840
Listen carefully.
One, this isn't even a case.

359
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:48,560
Two, if you want to investigate,
find another partner. Don't…

360
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:50,320
Don't bother you as you're about
to go back to being the deputy director.

361
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:51,720
I get it.

362
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,520
I knew you were that kind of person
from the start.

363
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:55,080
Just gaslighting people.

364
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:04,200
Did you scold me just now?

365
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:17,320
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

366
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:29,240
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH

367
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:37,880
‪This one is…

368
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,120
Kid.

369
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:48,120
Did you see Ran?

370
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:50,480
Lan? Who?

371
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,920
R-A-N.

372
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:53,960
You must be new here.

373
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,120
- I…
- He Yuanhang. Stop yelling.

374
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,440
Can't you see we're working here?

375
00:24:57,520 --> 00:24:59,280
I'm looking for Ran.

376
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,320
Something happened in Yuanlongli again?

377
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,960
Go back to your work.

378
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:06,200
Don't pester me.

379
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:11,280
Ran Fangxu is slacking
in the archive room.

380
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:13,360
Do talk to him.

381
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,560
He could've answered my call.

382
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:17,920
I called him for five minutes.

383
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,640
All of them are so lazy.

384
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,280
He is Mr. He.

385
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:31,360
Old Geezer. Why are you here again?

386
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:33,800
Don't call me old geezer.

387
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:34,920
Where is Ran?

388
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:37,840
Why do you need him?

389
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:41,160
It's none of your business. Where is he?

390
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,200
You eat to sleep, sleep to eat.

391
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:51,040
Where's your spirit?

392
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,400
Everyone gets bored
when they work here every day.

393
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:56,000
Why don't you ask them
to put me on patrol duty?

394
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,440
Ran Fangxu!

395
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,480
MEN'S TOILETS

396
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:21,560
UNDER MAINTENANCE

397
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,880
Ran Fangxu!

398
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:29,640
Ran Fangxu!

399
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:30,960
Just because you're standing
on the toilet bowl

400
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:32,600
doesn't mean I won't know you're here.

401
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,400
Come out. Open the door.

402
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,640
Sir. I have diarrhea.

403
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:37,920
I'm vomiting and pooping.

404
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,480
I can't go anywhere.

405
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:41,640
Are you an ostrich
that poops while standing?

406
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:43,200
Come out now.

407
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,520
I'll count to three.

408
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,960
Count to 300, and I still won't come out.

409
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:48,160
Just you wait.

410
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,320
- One.
- Sir.

411
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:51,800
- Two.
- What are you doing?

412
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:52,800
- Sir?
- Three!

413
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,320
Hey!

414
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,720
Sir,

415
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:07,720
I just finished this lesson plan.

416
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:13,080
Oh, you and your useless theories again.

417
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:16,520
I have a case that concerns my reputation.

418
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,160
You have a reputation?

419
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:19,640
I'll tell you on the way.

420
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:22,840
Sir, I have work to do.

421
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,640
Bah! This is what you call work?

422
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:27,320
Some people love to be on patrol duty.

423
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:29,840
Some people just want to stay
in the archive room.

424
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,280
I can't catch a break at all.

425
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:34,600
What are you implying?

426
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:41,960
Mister,

427
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:43,840
can you drive slower?

428
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:46,280
Slower?

429
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:49,400
Back then, on our first gig together,

430
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:53,560
I drove slightly faster
and you got your panties in a twist.

431
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:57,720
I… I have motion sickness.

432
00:27:58,440 --> 00:28:02,080
Besides, it wasn't like you drove fast
to investigate the case.

433
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,360
Nonsense!

434
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:06,960
Don't make it sound
like I'm irresponsible.

435
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:11,120
When we first worked together,

436
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,160
you didn't even bother memorizing
my surname.

437
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,040
I…

438
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:28,760
All right. This is it.

439
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:30,560
I'm not driving over there.

440
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,320
That place brings bad luck.

441
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:34,840
Pay up.

442
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:36,000
Okay.

443
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:37,120
Let's go.

444
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:41,040
You didn't tell me
we'd come to Yuanlongli.

445
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:44,000
Come on. If I told you,
you wouldn't want to come with me.

446
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:45,360
Come down now.

447
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,120
I'm just here on a business trip.

448
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,880
I'll be back after a week.

449
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,280
You're going back to Beijing after a week?

450
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,520
Did you bring me with you
for another case?

451
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:05,520
His name is Han Zi'ang.

452
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:07,480
He went missing less than 48 hours ago.

453
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:08,600
They haven't filed the case yet.

454
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,880
I've talked to the parents,

455
00:29:10,960 --> 00:29:13,360
and I think there's more
than meets the eye.

456
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:15,440
I agreed to help them.

457
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:19,280
After all these years, I've become
quite good at finding missing persons.

458
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:21,880
They call me human radar.

459
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:24,680
If there's more to the case
than meets the eye,

460
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,120
then hand the case over to the police.

461
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:28,240
As I said, they haven't
filed the case yet.

462
00:29:28,320 --> 00:29:31,520
I'm just a kind citizen who wants
to locate the missing child.

463
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:33,760
Since we're here already,
just help me out.

464
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:38,760
- My reputation is at stake here.
- Sir, I'm a teacher now.

465
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,920
And you're retired.
We can't investigate cases anymore.

466
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,400
Let's just leave.

467
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:43,680
Don't give me excuses.

468
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,040
Eighteen years ago,

469
00:29:45,120 --> 00:29:46,960
I too was eager to leave after a week.

470
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:50,000
But a jerk came to me
and said I was irresponsible.

471
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:57,760
Sorry, sir.

472
00:29:58,560 --> 00:29:59,760
Back then, it was my fault.

473
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:05,360
It's not your fault.
It's not anyone's fault.

474
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:07,080
If I must put the blame on something,

475
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:09,600
it's on the fact that you didn't build
a good relationship with me.

476
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,760
I didn't build
a good relationship with you?

477
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,840
- I kept addressing you as my mentor then.
- Nonsense!

478
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:17,760
Stop wasting my time. Get out of the car.

479
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:23,480
Slow down. Slow down.

480
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:30,040
You keep saying that you don't
want to come to Yuanlongli.

481
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:32,920
But once you're in here,
you walk briskly like an eager visitor.

482
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:36,280
That's because
you were gaslighting me again.

483
00:30:37,240 --> 00:30:40,520
I see you're not on social media.
It's not called gaslighting anymore.

484
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:42,600
It's called brainwashing. Come.

485
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:47,800
Let's take a break.

486
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:50,360
Don't. We can't stay here for long.

487
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:54,520
This building is haunted.
Once in a while, it'll kill someone.

488
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,920
Two policemen died here.

489
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:56,840
Died here?

490
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,720
One of them was in charge of this place.

491
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,200
- What's his name again?
- He something.

492
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:03,280
When they found him, his body was impaled

493
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:06,160
by a spear on this wall.

494
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:07,400
It was horrifying.

495
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:09,960
Quickly now.

496
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:12,320
You two look horrifying.

497
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:15,400
Mister. We weren't even talking about you.
Why are you yelling at me?

498
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:18,080
- Sir.
- Don't hold me back.

499
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:21,680
Tell me. How was I impaled on this wall?

500
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:30,120
Oh my…

501
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:42,800
Sir, Yuanlongli houses
a superstitious community.

502
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:44,200
You know that already.

503
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:45,680
Why pick a bone with them?

504
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:49,000
If I don't scold them now,
the next one they curse will be you.

505
00:31:57,680 --> 00:31:59,320
You're dead.

506
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:01,680
You can't step on the 18th floor.

507
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,440
<i>Yuanlongli</i>

508
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:08,960
- <i>Eighteenth floor, 18 pillars</i>
- <i>Eighteenth floor…</i>

509
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:14,480
<i>Eighteenth floor with 18 pillars</i>

510
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:19,600
<i>Eighteen pillars</i>
<i>With 18 men to carry them…</i>

511
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:22,720
They are still singing the nursery rhyme?

512
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:26,440
If you hadn't insisted
on investigating the truth,

513
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:30,040
this so-called haunted building
would've taken more lives.

514
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:36,240
<i>Eighteenth floor with 18 pillars</i>

515
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:41,360
<i>Eighteen bodies, 18 heads</i>

516
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:53,760
He Yuanhang.

517
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:55,560
You owe me a meal.

518
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,720
For what?

519
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:59,800
WEIYANG CULTURAL CENTER

520
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,120
Aren't you investigating a case?

521
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:03,720
I jumped the queue for you
and got the report ready.

522
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:08,160
Six more days till I return
to the police station.

523
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,240
What case is this?

524
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:11,680
Come on. They sent
the evidence for analysis.

525
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:13,480
Two sets of fingerprints.

526
00:33:13,560 --> 00:33:14,480
Four cigarette butts.

527
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:17,360
One cloak. And one security footage.

528
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:19,000
It's all under your name.

529
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:22,960
I…

530
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,040
It was all good.

531
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:29,960
Except Mr. He Yuanhang
and I don't get along well.

532
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:32,040
Can you get me another partner?

533
00:33:32,120 --> 00:33:33,840
Changing your partner on your first day?

534
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:35,080
What did He Yuanhang do?

535
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,800
I don't think he has…

536
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:40,520
Captain Feng. I'm here
to find my apprentice.

537
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:42,360
Let me reiterate.

538
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:43,640
I am not your apprentice.

539
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:47,680
Young and petty.
It's just a term. No need to overreact.

540
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:50,160
I'm not being petty.
I'm being responsible here.

541
00:33:51,080 --> 00:33:52,840
Captain Feng. See this?

542
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:55,080
Our temperaments don't match.
Our personalities are different.

543
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:57,360
We argue often,
and that'll affect our work efficiency.

544
00:33:57,440 --> 00:33:59,360
Since I'm going back
to the police station,

545
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:01,600
why don't you give him another partner?

546
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:03,760
I'll hand over whatever I'm doing to him.

547
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:10,920
I see you two are putting
on an act in front of me.

548
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:15,719
Just be frank. What help
do you need from me?

549
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:17,239
Captain Feng.

550
00:34:17,320 --> 00:34:19,400
This is not an act.

551
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:22,840
- I mean it. I want to break…
- Break up!

552
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,320
- Captain Feng.
- I am.

553
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:37,880
Captain Feng. The embarrassing case
from Yuanlongli.

554
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:39,719
The residents have come forward.

555
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:40,679
What now?

556
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:43,159
He Yuanhang. Mind your words.

557
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:48,920
Maybe officers like you
think it's nothing.

558
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:51,679
But the residents are getting manic.

559
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:55,239
They are saying the two missing persons
are the Black and White Guards.

560
00:34:55,320 --> 00:34:56,719
And the building is their hunting ground.

561
00:34:57,800 --> 00:34:59,720
And they are singing this.

562
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:01,120
<i>Yuanlongli</i>

563
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:02,680
<i>Eighteenth floor</i>

564
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:04,320
<i>Eighteen bodies, 18 heads</i>

565
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:05,320
Nonsense.

566
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:07,640
Someone among them
is trying to spread a rumor.

567
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,560
Captain Feng.

568
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:15,560
When they were building Yuanlongli,
they found a tomb.

569
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:17,120
It was a cenotaph
from the Three Kingdoms period.

570
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:18,400
There were no human remains inside.

571
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:21,320
The Residents Committee
just has to clarify the rumors.

572
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:23,920
Why mobilize the criminal police?

573
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:28,480
The problem is that Yuanlongli
is a complex neighborhood.

574
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:30,920
You see all sorts of people there.

575
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:33,240
Someone went missing yesterday.

576
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:34,440
Then today, a nursery song
like that appeared.

577
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:36,280
Everyone is scared.

578
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:39,080
- Please help us find the truth.
- He Yuanhang.

579
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:44,160
What was yesterday's case about?

580
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:47,000
Qu Dahai had already determined
that it was just a prank.

581
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:49,240
- But I…
- It wasn't a prank at all.

582
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,360
Captain Feng.

583
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:54,160
I interviewed the witnesses last night.

584
00:35:54,240 --> 00:35:55,360
I can confirm three things.

585
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:58,480
One. There are no footprints
deeper into the corridor.

586
00:35:58,560 --> 00:36:00,480
Two. The security guards
put the padlock there.

587
00:36:00,560 --> 00:36:03,800
Three. Mr. Liang broke the glass
of the door leading to the staircase.

588
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:06,840
Therefore, the exit path
Officer He described yesterday

589
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:08,440
could never have existed.

590
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:11,000
The disappearance of those two persons
is still an enigma.

591
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:17,560
Well said! I agree with Fangxu.

592
00:36:17,640 --> 00:36:18,720
I also agree with him.

593
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:21,800
Trivial problems, when neglected,
will fester into major problems.

594
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:24,840
Rumors can be destructive.

595
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:41,880
Some say that He Yuanhang
only got into the criminal department

596
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:43,240
because of his connections.

597
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:44,520
Take a seat.

598
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:51,160
But in fact, I chose him
from among many candidates.

599
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:52,520
Captain Feng.

600
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:55,280
Even though he never receives
proper training,

601
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:59,080
the place he's in charge of consistently

602
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,880
has the highest clearance rate.

603
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:02,600
What does this mean?

604
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:07,000
It means he has something
neither of us has.

605
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,960
In certain areas,
he will be quite helpful.

606
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:16,760
But of course, you can also
help him with your expertise.

607
00:37:16,840 --> 00:37:18,200
Do you get what I mean now?

608
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:22,280
Captain Feng,
about the case in Yuanlongli…

609
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:25,360
Both of you will follow up with the case.

610
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:29,880
Officer He. Don't let me keep you.
I have to go now.

611
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:34,920
‪POLICE BY THE PEOPLE
‪FOR THE PEOPLE

612
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:48,640
MISSING DOG

613
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:09,840
Stop.

614
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,160
Rewind a bit.

615
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:16,640
Here.

616
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:24,040
It looks like a cigarette.

617
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:26,400
Can you tell which brand it is?

618
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:31,480
No. No way.

619
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:33,920
No way.

620
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:44,600
It looks like

621
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:48,000
marks left by a medical paste.

622
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:54,400
What are you doing?

623
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:56,120
Did I sign this before you gave it
to the Forensic Department?

624
00:38:56,200 --> 00:38:57,880
Is the Forensic Department
strapped for cash lately?

625
00:38:57,960 --> 00:38:59,960
He Yuanhang! We're not done studying it.

626
00:39:00,040 --> 00:39:01,080
What does studying it serve?

627
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:02,960
Hey!

628
00:39:07,440 --> 00:39:10,000
MISSING PERSONS

629
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:16,160
MISSING PERSONS

630
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:19,120
FEMALE: AROUND 20-25 YEARS OLD
MALE: AROUND 55-60 YEARS OLD

631
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:23,360
This is your number?

632
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:24,960
Yes. Should I use yours?

633
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:27,040
I don't have a pager.

634
00:39:27,120 --> 00:39:28,560
Why do you not want to stay
in the criminal department?

635
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:29,840
You're too naive.

636
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:34,280
Officer He.

637
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:37,600
I believe we should first figure out
the motive behind their disappearance.

638
00:39:37,680 --> 00:39:39,840
Isn't it clear enough? It's a prank.

639
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:41,600
Then tell me.

640
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:43,600
Why did the woman take off her heels
when she entered the elevator?

641
00:39:43,680 --> 00:39:46,120
And why did she hold the heels
with her teeth?

642
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:48,840
Why did the old man press all the buttons
in the elevator before he left?

643
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,760
Because it's a prank. Understood?

644
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:52,960
Then why did they disappear
in that locked space?

645
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:54,480
- Why, why, why.
- Why did they…

646
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:56,240
Do you only know how to repeat why?

647
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:59,120
Our priority should be to find out
how they disappear in Yuanlongli.

648
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:01,080
That's redundant.

649
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:04,080
Find them, and you'll know
how they disappear.

650
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:05,400
Listen to me.

651
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:08,560
Find them, and they
will give you the answer.

652
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:11,800
Why should I listen to you?

653
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:15,040
Fine.

654
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:21,640
NANSHAN TYPEWRITING

655
00:40:22,560 --> 00:40:23,520
Wait.

656
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:25,920
You see those rickshaw riders?

657
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:28,840
Should we have a wager?

658
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:29,920
Go to them.

659
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:32,080
If you can get their names,

660
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:33,960
I'll take orders from you.

661
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:35,400
If you fail to do that,

662
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:37,280
you take orders from me.

663
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:38,360
What do you say?

664
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:40,560
No, thanks.

665
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:45,560
Didn't you want to find out how they left?

666
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:48,720
I remember the missing persons
came on a rickshaw.

667
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:02,520
Mister, where do you want to go?

668
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:03,440
Mister, where do you want to go?

669
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:05,560
- Mister, where do you want to go?
- Mister, where do you want to go?

670
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:07,280
Hello, everyone.

671
00:41:07,360 --> 00:41:08,960
I am from the criminal department
of Nanshan police station.

672
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:10,560
I'd like to know…

673
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:12,880
Hey!

674
00:41:14,680 --> 00:41:15,720
Hey…

675
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:19,400
Mister!

676
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:22,440
Mister!

677
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:33,840
Do you understand why I didn't leave
the police station's number?

678
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:36,040
You look like an imperial envoy
who visits a village.

679
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:38,080
Wearing a pair of slacks
won't make it easier to catch a criminal.

680
00:41:38,160 --> 00:41:39,640
You look posh.

681
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:41,520
You speak like an officer,

682
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:43,880
and you couldn't even get the names
of those rickshaw riders.

683
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:45,720
You're telling me you want
to investigate the case?

684
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:52,080
Officer He, when I was studying,

685
00:41:52,160 --> 00:41:54,520
I looked into renowned cases of missing
persons, both local and international.

686
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:56,840
Specifically, their psychology
and behavior.

687
00:41:56,920 --> 00:41:59,760
My judgment tells me that
the Yuanlongli case isn't just a prank.

688
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:05,320
Have you looked into the missing person
case in Weinan Street, Weiyang City?

689
00:42:07,240 --> 00:42:08,080
No.

690
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:09,600
Do you know why?

691
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:13,160
After I was assigned
to Weiyang, for 22 years,

692
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:17,080
whenever someone or even a pet

693
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:21,720
in my district went missing,
I could find them with my eyes closed.

694
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:24,720
I didn't need to study
renowned missing person cases.

695
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:28,640
But hanging up posters
and waiting for calls is too passive.

696
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:30,840
And your initiatives
bring trouble to others.

697
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:32,160
To whom?

698
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:34,080
When you sent the evidence
to the Forensic Department,

699
00:42:34,160 --> 00:42:35,320
why did you leave my name?

700
00:42:37,200 --> 00:42:40,160
I only came here yesterday.
They won't acknowledge my signature.

701
00:42:44,080 --> 00:42:46,400
Get out of the car.
Get yourself back to the station

702
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:48,480
and withdraw all analysis requests
under my name.

703
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:52,800
Take me to Yuanlongli.
I'll examine the scene again.

704
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:54,760
Did I owe you a favor? Get out of the car.

705
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,800
It's an official vehicle.
Why should I leave?

706
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:58,120
Official vehicle?

707
00:42:58,200 --> 00:42:59,680
This is my personal car.

708
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:01,320
I paid for the petrol from my own pocket.

709
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,080
And I printed these things
with my own money.

710
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:06,360
You think you're the only one
with integrity? I have it too.

711
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:09,200
Get out of the car.

712
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:11,640
Officer He.

713
00:43:11,720 --> 00:43:13,640
Based on my deduction,

714
00:43:13,720 --> 00:43:15,640
the unusual behavior
from those two missing persons

715
00:43:15,720 --> 00:43:18,200
seems to be motivated
by some external coercion.

716
00:43:18,280 --> 00:43:20,360
Many homicides also started
as a missing person case.

717
00:43:20,440 --> 00:43:21,960
What homicide?

718
00:43:22,040 --> 00:43:24,640
There has never been a murder on my turf.

719
00:43:24,720 --> 00:43:26,960
You came, and there's a murder
all of a sudden.

720
00:43:28,280 --> 00:43:31,040
Murphy's law. Whatever you don't
want to happen will happen.

721
00:43:31,120 --> 00:43:33,280
I don’t care about your law.
I don’t care about your homicide.

722
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:35,320
You lost the bet just now.

723
00:43:35,400 --> 00:43:38,040
So you take orders from me.
I now order you to return to the station

724
00:43:38,120 --> 00:43:40,240
and withdraw the analysis requests
under my name.

725
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:41,240
He Yuanhang!

726
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:43,720
You do not have what it takes
to be a criminal police officer.

727
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:44,440
PATTIA CLUB, THAI MASSAGE
